01:02:42.420 --> 01:02:46.850
Look, what else do you kids
want for that plate?

259
01:02:46.850 --> 01:02:53.060
Noodles was telling me about Bugsy.
Seems he's boss, thanks to you.

260
01:02:53.060 --> 01:02:56.360
- Meaning what?
- Meaning he pays you off.

261
01:02:56.360 --> 01:03:00.230
Will you slow down?
What is your hurry? Take it easy.

262
01:03:00.230 --> 01:03:03.720
If you keep this up,
you're gonna come too fast.

263
01:03:04.740 --> 01:03:09.280
> Do you see what I mean? You're
so stupid. I can't believe it.

264
01:03:09.280 --> 01:03:14.990
So why does Bugsy pay you?
What do you do for him?

265
01:03:15.830 --> 01:03:20.210
- I close an eye once in a while.
- Well, now you close an eye for us.

266
01:03:20.210 --> 01:03:23.820
Why? What are you kids up to?

267
01:03:27.260 --> 01:03:28.930
He'll tell you.

268
01:03:28.930 --> 01:03:33.810
Me, him, Cockeye and Patsy,
we're working together.

269
01:03:33.810 --> 01:03:35.390
Bugsy'll flatten you.

270
01:03:35.390 --> 01:03:38.900
Besides, I don't put up
with no trouble on my beat.

271
01:03:38.900 --> 01:03:40.860
You'll put up, and you'll shut up.

272
01:03:40.860 --> 01:03:43.150
You hear nothing,
and you see nothing.

273
01:03:43.150 --> 01:03:45.190
Just like you did for Bugsy.

274
01:03:45.190 --> 01:03:46.820
Shit!

275
01:03:46.820 --> 01:03:52.030
Don't get upset. That makes it
worse. It can happen the first time.

276
01:03:52.030 --> 01:03:53.620
It's them two talking out there.

277
01:03:53.620 --> 01:03:56.540
Can't you see you're ruining
the mood?

278
01:03:56.540 --> 01:03:59.620
We made our deal.

279
01:03:59.620 --> 01:04:03.700
- So take a walk.
- Come here, honey.

280
01:04:05.300 --> 01:04:09.530
- Feel good, bubeleh?
- He'll never get it up.

281
01:04:10.470 --> 01:04:16.460
Relax. Okay.
Calm down, calm down.

282
01:04:20.440 --> 01:04:25.470
Okay. Okay, come here.

283
01:05:44.850 --> 01:05:46.940
I'm glad the baby's better.

284
01:05:46.940 --> 01:05:51.680
- Happy Pesach, Deborah.
- Happy Pesach, Becky.

285
01:05:57.280 --> 01:05:59.910
Hurry. We're gonna be late.

286
01:05:59.910 --> 01:06:02.910
- There's Deborah.
- Sorry. Mama needed help.

287
01:06:02.910 --> 01:06:08.200
Good girl. I just locked up,
and I'm giving you the keys.

288
01:06:20.720 --> 01:06:24.970
I thought I'd just practice
my dance routines. All right?

289
01:06:24.970 --> 01:06:28.630
Make sure you don't let
the goyim in.

290
01:06:29.230 --> 01:06:33.310
- Okay, bye.
- See you later, Debbie. Bye.

291
01:07:45.470 --> 01:07:48.010
Get down off of there,
roach.

292
01:07:48.010 --> 01:07:49.930
That record's just like Ex-Lax.

293
01:07:49.930 --> 01:07:54.090
Every time I put it on,
you have to go to the bathroom.

294
01:08:11.200 --> 01:08:12.950
What are you doing?

295
01:08:12.950 --> 01:08:16.000
- Give me a drink.
- We're closed.

296
01:08:16.000 --> 01:08:20.710
Nice people don't drink on Pesach.
They go to the synagogue.

297
01:08:20.710 --> 01:08:22.880
So, what are you doing here?

298
01:08:22.880 --> 01:08:25.800
Somebody's got to keep an eye
on the place.

299
01:08:25.800 --> 01:08:28.180
There are a lot of thieves
out there.

300
01:08:28.180 --> 01:08:30.220
One could get into your house.

301
01:08:30.220 --> 01:08:33.800
Especially if you leave
the door open.

302
01:09:05.670 --> 01:09:08.170
You can pray here too.

303
01:09:09.760 --> 01:09:14.000
Here or in the synagogue,
to God it's the same difference.

304
01:09:15.180 --> 01:09:17.840
Come over here and sit down.

305
01:09:50.510 --> 01:09:53.550
"My beloved is white and ruddy.

306
01:09:53.550 --> 01:09:57.350
His skin is as the most fine gold.

307
01:09:57.350 --> 01:10:01.800
His cheeks are as a bed of spices."

308
01:10:04.140 --> 01:10:08.380
Even though he hasn't washed
since last December.

309
01:10:12.280 --> 01:10:15.360
"His eyes are as the eyes
of doves.

310
01:10:15.360 --> 01:10:18.240
His body is as bright ivory.

311
01:10:18.240 --> 01:10:22.570
His legs are as pillars of marble."

312
01:10:24.040 --> 01:10:27.320
In pants so dirty
they stand by themselves.

313
01:10:28.710 --> 01:10:32.320
"He is altogether lovable."

314
01:10:33.510 --> 01:10:36.220
But he'll always be
a two-bit punk...

315
01:10:36.220 --> 01:10:41.550
...so he'll never be my beloved.
What a shame.

316
01:11:12.540 --> 01:11:14.740
Somebody's there.

317
01:11:26.930 --> 01:11:29.260
There ain't nobody.

318
01:11:35.360 --> 01:11:36.730
It's Max.

319
01:11:36.730 --> 01:11:40.570
So that's who it was.

320
01:11:40.570 --> 01:11:42.600
Noodles!

321
01:11:46.530 --> 01:11:49.610
Go on, run.
Your mother's calling you.

322
01:11:55.290 --> 01:11:57.070
Noodles!

323
01:11:57.880 --> 01:12:00.750
Just gonna go see what he wants.

324
01:12:29.540 --> 01:12:32.740
- Hey.
- Yo?

325
01:12:35.250 --> 01:12:38.860
- You been here long?
- No.

326
01:12:39.550 --> 01:12:42.200
Were you in there?

327
01:12:44.170 --> 01:12:46.550
You're one lousy kisser.

328
01:12:46.550 --> 01:12:49.890
I seen you go in there
after that ball-buster.

329
01:12:49.890 --> 01:12:51.680
Here's the stuff from last night.

330
01:12:51.680 --> 01:12:55.140
We got 4 for the silverware,
6 for the typewriter.

331
01:12:55.140 --> 01:12:59.720
Lipschitz wouldn't cough up any
more. We gotta get somebody else.

332
01:13:01.650 --> 01:13:04.740
I came to divvy up.

333
01:13:04.740 --> 01:13:09.770
- Tomorrow, with the others.
- I also came to pick you up.

334
01:13:10.830 --> 01:13:15.040
- I can't come right now. -The
houses, the stores are all empty.

335
01:13:15.040 --> 01:13:19.170
We got our pick. You pick that.

336
01:13:19.170 --> 01:13:21.540
Yeah.

337
01:13:24.170 --> 01:13:29.080
Some partner I got. Have fun.

338
01:13:34.520 --> 01:13:36.810
How's it going, boys?

339
01:13:36.810 --> 01:13:39.350
Who's that?

340
01:13:39.350 --> 01:13:41.720
Bugsy.

341
01:13:58.580 --> 01:14:02.210
I hear you guys are in business
for yourselves now.

342
01:14:02.210 --> 01:14:04.530
I hear youse are doing real good.

343
01:14:11.380 --> 01:14:15.000
Ain't you gonna introduce me
to your friend here?

344
01:14:17.060 --> 01:14:20.010
I'll introduce myself.

345
01:14:24.520 --> 01:14:26.800
Excuse the glove.

346
01:14:36.160 --> 01:14:38.150
Son of a bitch!

347
01:15:25.160 --> 01:15:27.460
That's my cut.

348
01:15:27.460 --> 01:15:31.630
You don't work for me,
you don't work for no one.

349
01:15:31.630 --> 01:15:33.880
I don't like bosses.

350
01:15:33.880 --> 01:15:37.790
You was better off
you stayed in the Bronx.

351
01:15:40.640 --> 01:15:44.050
It would have been better
for you too.

352
01:16:25.680 --> 01:16:30.310
- I'm gonna kill him
one of these days. NOODLES: Yeah?

353
01:16:30.310 --> 01:16:35.180
Meantime it looks like
he's killed us.

354
01:16:54.040 --> 01:16:57.290
Deborah, open up the door.

355
01:16:58.040 --> 01:17:01.450
Deborah, open up the door.

356
01:17:02.550 --> 01:17:04.580
Deborah.

357
01:17:46.220 --> 01:17:50.450
- That stuff, is it ready?
- We're loading it.

358
01:18:24.630 --> 01:18:26.920
Che cazzo succede down here?

359
01:18:26.920 --> 01:18:29.550
AI, we got the big boys
with us today.

360
01:18:29.550 --> 01:18:33.470
- They wanna work for us. -Doing what
Bugsy did. We want his job.

361
01:18:33.470 --> 01:18:34.810
Do you get that?

362
01:18:34.810 --> 01:18:40.550
We the best escorts
you ever gonna get.

363
01:18:40.980 --> 01:18:45.230
A fangulo a ma, escort
your mother's ass out of here.

364
01:18:45.230 --> 01:18:47.480
Okay. Let's go, Noodles.

365
01:18:47.480 --> 01:18:50.890
We'll peddle your invention
somewhere else.

366
01:18:52.240 --> 01:18:54.740
Hey, wait a minute.

367
01:18:56.160 --> 01:18:57.370
What invention?

368
01:18:57.370 --> 01:19:00.500
- You ship your stuff by the river,
right? -Sometimes.

369
01:19:00.500 --> 01:19:04.210
And when you get caught,
you throw the cases overboard.

370
01:19:04.210 --> 01:19:07.130
- You lose the whole shipment.
- So?

371
01:19:07.130 --> 01:19:10.010
For 10 percent,
we'll save it all for you.

372
01:19:10.010 --> 01:19:13.740
- What do you got, a submarine?
- We got salt.

373
01:19:14.220 --> 01:19:15.930
You got what?

374
01:19:15.930 --> 01:19:18.100
Me and the boys are rolling salts.

375
01:19:18.100 --> 01:19:20.980
We need 3 tons of salt per shipment.

376
01:19:20.980 --> 01:19:24.980
Get the fuck out of here.
Go back to school where you belong.

377
01:19:24.980 --> 01:19:27.610
What is it with all this salt?

378
01:19:27.610 --> 01:19:32.560
Hey, hey, we got salt
on our noodles. Show 'em.

379
01:19:44.870 --> 01:19:47.070
This is full of salt.

380
01:19:51.840 --> 01:19:53.830
All right, come here.

381
01:20:08.560 --> 01:20:11.400
- So?
- Keep your shirt on.

382
01:20:11.400 --> 01:20:14.430
We gotta wait for the salt
to dissolve.

383
01:20:46.230 --> 01:20:49.550
- Well?
- Hey, what's wrong?

384
01:20:55.280 --> 01:20:57.360
Hey, look.

385
01:20:57.360 --> 01:20:59.110
Wow!

386
01:21:00.910 --> 01:21:02.650
Great!

387
01:21:03.700 --> 01:21:06.370
- Look at that!
- It's great.

388
01:21:06.370 --> 01:21:08.190
- Noodles.
- Look.

389
01:21:09.460 --> 01:21:13.360
- I see 'em! What did I say?
- Yeah.

390
01:21:16.460 --> 01:21:18.160
Yeah!

391
01:21:26.430 --> 01:21:31.470
- Hey, Noodles.
- Hooray. Hooray for us!

392
01:21:34.980 --> 01:21:36.630
We did it.

393
01:21:37.400 --> 01:21:39.270
Come here, Max.

394
01:21:40.360 --> 01:21:44.070
- We did it.
- No, Max, no!

395
01:21:47.410 --> 01:21:49.060
Max.

396
01:21:50.330 --> 01:21:52.150
Max.

397
01:22:03.420 --> 01:22:05.170
Max!

398
01:22:07.350 --> 01:22:09.000
Max!

399
01:22:23.030 --> 01:22:25.770
What would you do without me?

400
01:23:30.970 --> 01:23:32.670
There.

401
01:23:35.600 --> 01:23:39.060
From here on, we establish
the shared funds of the gang.

402
01:23:39.060 --> 01:23:42.190
They belong to all of us together
and to none of us alone.

403
01:23:42.190 --> 01:23:46.360
And we solemnly swear to put in
50 percent of everything we make.

404
01:23:46.360 --> 01:23:48.600
- Agreed?
- Agreed.

405
01:23:49.280 --> 01:23:51.430
- Agreed.
- Agreed.

406
01:23:54.200 --> 01:23:55.850
Agreed.

407
01:23:57.950 --> 01:24:00.280
I wanna take another peek.

408
01:24:38.410 --> 01:24:42.250
This goes to Fat Moe.
We don't tell him what it's for.

409
01:24:42.250 --> 01:24:45.790
And he gives it back
only when we're all together.

410
01:24:45.790 --> 01:24:47.410
Agreed?

411
01:24:48.080 --> 01:24:49.740
Agreed.

412
01:24:53.220 --> 01:24:55.040
Agreed.

413
01:25:52.230 --> 01:25:54.630
Bugsy's coming! Run!

414
01:26:45.990 --> 01:26:47.730
Noodles.

415
01:26:48.870 --> 01:26:51.360
I slipped.

416
01:28:32.590 --> 01:28:35.170
Schmuck.

417
01:30:49.770 --> 01:30:51.760
Wanna go in?

418
01:30:55.320 --> 01:30:57.150
Yeah.

419
01:30:57.150 --> 01:30:58.930
You a relative?

420
01:31:02.360 --> 01:31:04.020
An uncle.

421
01:31:16.210 --> 01:31:17.960
It's open.

422
01:34:29.560 --> 01:34:33.190
"Erected to their everlasting memory
by their friend and brother...

423
01:34:33.190 --> 01:34:35.970
...David Aaronson, 1967."

424
01:34:57.680 --> 01:35:00.800
Hello. May I help you?

425
01:35:01.220 --> 01:35:05.180
- I was just looking.
- I'm the director of Riverdale.

426
01:35:05.180 --> 01:35:07.890
I've never seen a tomb like this.

427
01:35:07.890 --> 01:35:12.380
We like to call them "heavens",
we find it's more calming.

428
01:35:16.730 --> 01:35:19.490
Erected to their everlasting memory
by their friend and brother...

429
01:35:19.490 --> 01:35:22.450
David Aaronson, 1967.

430
01:35:22.450 --> 01:35:24.940
Is it a new building?

431
01:35:26.500 --> 01:35:31.480
Yes. Do you know Mr. Aaronson,
Mr...? Sorry.

432
01:35:32.790 --> 01:35:34.660
Mr. Williams.

433
01:35:35.420 --> 01:35:41.500
Mr. Williams. An interest like yours
is a compliment to our architects.

434
01:35:42.680 --> 01:35:44.420
After you.

435
01:36:12.210 --> 01:36:15.920
I think the beauty of the interior
equals that of the exterior.

436
01:36:15.920 --> 01:36:18.570
Don't you agree, Mr. Williams?

437
01:36:19.210 --> 01:36:22.010
We wanted to do
the style of the 30s,

438
01:36:22.010 --> 01:36:25.580
which is when our young friends
went away.

439
01:36:33.980 --> 01:36:36.980
Was it Mr. Aaronson's idea?

440
01:36:36.980 --> 01:36:40.840
Actually he left the whole thing
up to us.

441
01:36:41.570 --> 01:36:44.320
We had carte blanche.

442
01:36:45.030 --> 01:36:47.490
All he suggested was
the inscription.

443
01:36:47.490 --> 01:36:51.650
"Your youngest and strongest
will fall by the sword."

444
01:36:54.200 --> 01:36:57.210
- What about the music?
- And the music.

445
01:36:57.210 --> 01:37:00.210
- That was exactly his suggestion?
- Yes.

446
01:37:00.210 --> 01:37:02.710
We received a tape.

447
01:37:03.510 --> 01:37:06.130
You seem to know him so well.

448
01:37:06.130 --> 01:37:10.050
I'd like to ask you to tell him
how much you like the "heaven",

449
01:37:10.050 --> 01:37:14.210
- when you see him.
Could you do that? -Sure.

450
01:37:15.060 --> 01:37:19.150
I've been away quite a long time
and I lost the address.

451
01:37:19.150 --> 01:37:21.230
Maybe you...

452
01:37:21.230 --> 01:37:24.600
You must have signed a bill
or something.

453
01:37:25.820 --> 01:37:29.430
The bank handled it.
A foreign bank.

454
01:37:30.860 --> 01:37:34.600
I wish I could be of more assistance
to you, Mr. Williams.

455
01:37:37.200 --> 01:37:40.360
Have you ever thought to build
your own heaven?

456
01:38:14.780 --> 01:38:16.940
Think about it.

457
01:40:46.720 --> 01:40:49.380
Can I take that for you, sir?

458
01:40:51.390 --> 01:40:53.840
Your limousine is waiting.

459
01:41:03.860 --> 01:41:05.610
Maxie.

460
01:41:17.170 --> 01:41:20.540
How are you, uncle?
You're looking good.

461
01:41:21.590 --> 01:41:23.790
You're looking a little better.

462
01:41:26.930 --> 01:41:31.290
Come on. Better get you
off the streets.

463
01:41:34.100 --> 01:41:37.730
- Some limousine.
- What are you talking, huh?

464
01:41:37.730 --> 01:41:42.440
We own the company now.
It's a good cover. It pays off too.

465
01:41:42.440 --> 01:41:46.730
My mother wrote me you was
in the body-snatching business.

466
01:41:48.660 --> 01:41:52.120
I appreciate everything you did
for my family.

467
01:41:52.120 --> 01:41:55.000
Forget it. It's your dough.

468
01:41:55.000 --> 01:41:59.170
It's all down in black and white
in the company books.

469
01:41:59.170 --> 01:42:02.090
You're the company.
You and Patsy and Cockeye.

470
01:42:02.090 --> 01:42:04.800
Gravediggers and partners.

471
01:42:04.800 --> 01:42:08.330
Hey, enough of this.
Business before pleasure.

472
01:42:08.760 --> 01:42:11.260
We got a rush job. Here.

473
01:42:13.720 --> 01:42:16.920
Come here. Look at this. Come here.

474
01:42:18.390 --> 01:42:22.510
Sudden death. Fucking tragedy, huh?

475
01:42:23.440 --> 01:42:27.440
- 26 years old.
- 26?

476
01:42:27.440 --> 01:42:32.950
- What a shame. -Great stiff.
She died of an overdose.

477
01:42:32.950 --> 01:42:35.120
And I'm ready for another.

478
01:42:35.120 --> 01:42:39.030
Pump the life into her. You didn't
turn pansy in there, did you?

479
01:42:42.330 --> 01:42:44.200
There you go.

480
01:42:46.760 --> 01:42:51.210
Turning over in the grave.
They do it every time.

481
01:43:32.130 --> 01:43:35.040
Don't worry. A pansy he ain't.

482
01:43:37.640 --> 01:43:40.770
- Thanks.
- You're welcome, Noodles.

483
01:43:40.770 --> 01:43:42.890
Whoops. Sorry.

484
01:43:42.890 --> 01:43:45.770
Thanks. Good night.

485
01:43:45.770 --> 01:43:48.440
Hey, you want a little
pick-me-up?

486
01:43:48.440 --> 01:43:51.220
No, thanks. I've had mine.

487
01:43:52.440 --> 01:43:56.930
- Did you give her your all?
- What do you think? You bet.

488
01:44:21.220 --> 01:44:24.270
Wait till you see this place.

489
01:44:24.270 --> 01:44:26.140
It's over here.

490
01:44:28.020 --> 01:44:32.050
- Where we going?
- To a place that never closes.

491
01:44:32.570 --> 01:44:34.970
Whoops. Watch yourself.

492
01:44:52.040 --> 01:44:53.250
What's this?

493
01:44:53.250 --> 01:44:56.160
Our place.
We got the hottest spot in town.

494
01:45:02.800 --> 01:45:06.790
This is the real Fat Moe's.

495
01:45:07.770 --> 01:45:10.140
Get rid of that rag, will you?

496
01:45:11.020 --> 01:45:13.610
- What do you think?
- It's beautiful.

497
01:45:13.610 --> 01:45:16.350
- You like it?
- Beautiful. Beautiful.

498
01:45:31.370 --> 01:45:33.570
Hey, give me that.

499
01:45:38.420 --> 01:45:41.800
- Noodles.
- Patsy, look.

500
01:45:41.800 --> 01:45:45.830
Come here, son of a bitch.
Come here!

501
01:45:46.760 --> 01:45:49.220
- You look fantastic.
- Wait a minute.

502
01:45:49.220 --> 01:45:51.000
How you doing?

503
01:45:53.480 --> 01:45:55.850
- Look how big you got.
- Me?

504
01:45:55.850 --> 01:45:58.310
Noodles. Oh, God.

505
01:45:58.730 --> 01:46:01.890
- Noodles!
- Number three coming through.

506
01:46:05.740 --> 01:46:09.660
Let's have a toast, for chrissakes!

507
01:46:09.660 --> 01:46:12.450
- You look like shit.
- I just got out of prison.

508
01:46:12.450 --> 01:46:15.080
- Nice guy.
- Hey, Noodles, get a load of this.

509
01:46:15.080 --> 01:46:16.980
