1243
03:17:11.910 --> 03:17:16.200
Just long enough so he can get
the idea out of his mind.

1244
03:17:17.580 --> 03:17:23.120
If you can't stand being away
from him, put yourself there too.

1245
03:17:24.300 --> 03:17:27.630
Better off than being dead.

1246
03:17:31.640 --> 03:17:34.340
You know what to do.

1247
03:17:37.560 --> 03:17:40.810
And if you don't, I will.

1248
03:17:43.820 --> 03:17:45.240
Get out!

1249
03:17:45.240 --> 03:17:49.890
Take a cab. I'm busy.
I got things to do. Get out.

1250
03:17:55.040 --> 03:17:56.560
Noodles.

1251
03:17:57.210 --> 03:18:00.530
Make up your mind fast, huh?

1252
03:19:24.830 --> 03:19:27.420
What's the matter?

1253
03:19:27.420 --> 03:19:30.320
Aren't you having a good time?

1254
03:19:36.720 --> 03:19:39.850
Why are you going out tonight?

1255
03:19:39.850 --> 03:19:43.500
Why bother now that prohibition
is almost over?

1256
03:19:45.140 --> 03:19:49.230
Everybody's selling. We got friends
who wanna get rid of booze.

1257
03:19:49.230 --> 03:19:54.090
Practically nothing.
So we figured, why not.

1258
03:19:59.870 --> 03:20:02.950
I'm gonna be gone for a while.

1259
03:20:02.950 --> 03:20:06.280
I'll be waiting at the hotel.

1260
03:20:06.710 --> 03:20:11.240
I like it when you come home
late and wake me up.

1261
03:20:16.420 --> 03:20:19.040
I'm not gonna be home tonight.

1262
03:20:25.640 --> 03:20:28.640
I'm not gonna be home tomorrow
either.

1263
03:20:28.640 --> 03:20:33.010
I thought these things
only take a couple of hours.

1264
03:20:38.990 --> 03:20:45.200
Ladies and gents, I drink to
the demise of Fat Moe's speakeasy.

1265
03:20:45.200 --> 03:20:50.000
Who the hell wants to drink
here legally anyway, am I right?

1266
03:20:50.000 --> 03:20:53.900
Okay. Come on, Moe, set them up.
Go on, get in there.

1267
03:21:08.520 --> 03:21:11.170
Here's mud in your eye.

1268
03:21:17.440 --> 03:21:19.340
Boys.

1269
03:21:22.320 --> 03:21:24.610
Let's drink to our last shipment.

1270
03:21:24.610 --> 03:21:27.620
There's more onboard
tonight than just booze.

1271
03:21:27.620 --> 03:21:33.210
It's 10 years of our lives. Ten
years that were really worth living.

1272
03:21:33.210 --> 03:21:34.990
Yeah.

1273
03:21:53.060 --> 03:21:55.300
Noodles.

1274
03:21:56.270 --> 03:21:58.270
Noodles.

1275
03:21:59.560 --> 03:22:02.560
- L'Chaim.
- L'Chaim.

1276
03:22:05.150 --> 03:22:08.150
How long will I have to wait?

1277
03:22:11.410 --> 03:22:15.320
A year and a half, more or less.

1278
03:22:16.290 --> 03:22:18.920
Six months off for good behavior.

1279
03:22:18.920 --> 03:22:22.160
- What are you gonna do?
- Don't ask.

1280
03:23:56.510 --> 03:23:58.760
FEMALE OPERATOR: Operator.

1281
03:23:59.680 --> 03:24:01.260
Police, please.

1282
03:24:06.860 --> 03:24:09.510
Fifth Precinct. Sergeant Halloran.

1283
03:24:11.860 --> 03:24:13.810
Hello.

1284
03:24:14.360 --> 03:24:17.620
Who's speaking? Can I help you?

1285
03:24:17.620 --> 03:24:20.020
- Hello.
- Yeah.

1286
03:24:22.200 --> 03:24:24.360
I got a good tip for you.

1287
03:24:50.440 --> 03:24:54.640
- Yeah, who is it?
- It's Max. Open the door.

1288
03:25:00.110 --> 03:25:04.330
- What's the matter with you?
You sick? -No, I'm fine.

1289
03:25:04.330 --> 03:25:06.400
You don't look it.

1290
03:25:08.120 --> 03:25:11.460
Maybe you'd better stay home
tonight, huh?

1291
03:25:11.460 --> 03:25:14.790
- Why?
- Huh.

1292
03:25:16.840 --> 03:25:20.170
You know, I've been watching you
all night.

1293
03:25:21.260 --> 03:25:24.510
And you've been drinking
like a fish.

1294
03:25:24.970 --> 03:25:27.800
Trying to get your courage up?

1295
03:25:30.900 --> 03:25:34.600
We're only bringing
in a shipment of booze.

1296
03:25:35.730 --> 03:25:39.340
It's got so you're even scared
to do that.

1297
03:25:40.700 --> 03:25:43.850
Maybe you just better
stay home tonight.

1298
03:25:44.490 --> 03:25:46.440
With Eve.

1299
03:25:56.380 --> 03:26:01.210
Hey, Maxie, everywhere you go,
I go too. Remember that.

1300
03:26:10.640 --> 03:26:13.270
Maybe Sharkey was right.

1301
03:26:13.270 --> 03:26:16.470
Maybe I ought to just dump you.

1302
03:26:25.200 --> 03:26:29.330
- You're really crazy.
- Never say that.

1303
03:26:29.330 --> 03:26:32.900
Don't say it!

1304
03:26:39.380 --> 03:26:43.630
Max made fools of us,
Noodles. He wanted to die.

1305
03:26:43.630 --> 03:26:46.840
Did you know his old man died
in the nut house?

1306
03:26:46.840 --> 03:26:49.890
Max didn't want to end up
the same way.

1307
03:26:49.890 --> 03:26:54.180
So he put the idea
in our heads to tip off the cops.

1308
03:26:54.180 --> 03:26:59.230
And when they stopped the truck,
Max started shooting first

1309
03:26:59.230 --> 03:27:02.930
just to get himself killed.

1310
03:27:19.710 --> 03:27:22.460
What is this?

1311
03:27:25.090 --> 03:27:26.660
Opening night.

1312
03:27:27.930 --> 03:27:31.050
Fifteen years ago.

1313
03:27:31.050 --> 03:27:33.460
Who's this?

1314
03:27:34.770 --> 03:27:38.170
Patron saint of the place.

1315
03:27:39.140 --> 03:27:42.190
And some actress.

1316
03:27:42.190 --> 03:27:43.970
Do you know her?

1317
03:27:45.570 --> 03:27:47.520
No.

1318
03:28:15.800 --> 03:28:18.300
This proves me base:

1319
03:28:19.270 --> 03:28:22.230
If she first meet the curled Antony,
he'll make demand of her,

1320
03:28:22.230 --> 03:28:25.840
and spend that kiss
which is my heaven to have.

1321
03:28:48.800 --> 03:28:51.540
Come, thou mortal wretch,

1322
03:28:53.800 --> 03:28:58.880
with thy sharp teeth this knot
intrinsicate of life at once untie:

1323
03:29:01.140 --> 03:29:03.760
poor venomous fool.

1324
03:29:05.690 --> 03:29:09.140
Be angry, and dispatch.

1325
03:29:11.530 --> 03:29:14.770
Oh, couldst thou speak,

1326
03:29:15.280 --> 03:29:19.660
that I might hear thee call
great Caesar ass unpolicied!

1327
03:29:19.660 --> 03:29:22.540
Oh eastern star! Peace, peace!

1328
03:29:22.540 --> 03:29:25.000
Dost thou not see my baby
at my breast,

1329
03:29:25.000 --> 03:29:28.670
that sucks the nurse asleep?
Oh, break! Oh, break!

1330
03:29:28.670 --> 03:29:31.460
As sweet as balm,

1331
03:29:31.460 --> 03:29:35.750
as soft as air, as gentle...

1332
03:29:37.050 --> 03:29:39.370
Oh, Antony!

1333
03:29:47.180 --> 03:29:49.720
Nay, I will take thee too.

1334
03:29:57.110 --> 03:29:59.490
What should I stay...

1335
03:29:59.490 --> 03:30:03.220
In this vile world?
So, fare thee well.

1336
03:30:03.950 --> 03:30:08.960
Now boast thee, death, in thy
possession lies a lass unparallel'd.

1337
03:30:08.960 --> 03:30:11.170
Downy windows, close,

1338
03:30:11.170 --> 03:30:15.670
and golden Phoebus never be beheld
of eyes again so royal!

1339
03:30:15.670 --> 03:30:19.450
Your crown's awry.
I'll mend it, and then play.

1340
03:30:56.710 --> 03:30:59.410
Hello, Deborah.

1341
03:31:06.600 --> 03:31:09.670
Aren't you gonna say anything?

1342
03:31:16.020 --> 03:31:19.980
What is someone
supposed to say after...

1343
03:31:19.980 --> 03:31:23.440
...more than 30 years.

1344
03:31:28.160 --> 03:31:33.770
Well, how about, "How you doing?
You're looking good." Or...

1345
03:31:36.120 --> 03:31:39.700
"I was hoping
I'd never see you again."

1346
03:31:41.710 --> 03:31:45.120
I never thought I would.

1347
03:31:45.800 --> 03:31:48.850
There's a difference.

1348
03:31:48.850 --> 03:31:51.310
At least you recognized me,
that's something.

1349
03:31:51.310 --> 03:31:55.540
Actresses have good memories.

1350
03:32:04.900 --> 03:32:07.650
You want a drink?

1351
03:32:11.450 --> 03:32:14.280
I'm having one.

1352
03:32:24.300 --> 03:32:25.740
Margo.

1353
03:32:27.090 --> 03:32:29.970
- Yes, miss?
- That's all. You can go.

1354
03:32:29.970 --> 03:32:32.590
All right, miss.

1355
03:32:37.060 --> 03:32:40.270
She called you "miss."

1356
03:32:40.270 --> 03:32:43.090
You never got married?

1357
03:32:43.520 --> 03:32:45.550
No.

1358
03:32:48.740 --> 03:32:50.680
You live alone?

1359
03:32:58.410 --> 03:33:00.320
No.

1360
03:33:06.750 --> 03:33:09.500
Where were you?

1361
03:33:12.010 --> 03:33:14.830
I was out of town.

1362
03:33:17.260 --> 03:33:20.470
Have you been back long?

1363
03:33:21.020 --> 03:33:23.600
A couple of days.

1364
03:33:23.600 --> 03:33:26.260
Are you staying?

1365
03:33:37.490 --> 03:33:39.310
That depends.

1366
03:33:41.830 --> 03:33:44.320
Why do you want to see me?

1367
03:33:45.750 --> 03:33:48.250
Two reasons.

1368
03:33:48.250 --> 03:33:51.510
First, I wanted to see
if you did the right thing,

1369
03:33:51.510 --> 03:33:54.000
turning me down
to become an actress.

1370
03:33:57.930 --> 03:33:59.920
Well?

1371
03:34:02.180 --> 03:34:05.010
You did. You're terrific.

1372
03:34:20.200 --> 03:34:23.490
"Age cannot wither her."

1373
03:34:23.490 --> 03:34:26.900
It's like the play
was written for you.

1374
03:34:29.960 --> 03:34:32.630
What was the other reason?

1375
03:34:32.630 --> 03:34:35.330
The other reason...

1376
03:34:38.130 --> 03:34:42.870
...is to decide whether I should go
to a party tomorrow night.

1377
03:34:49.190 --> 03:34:51.130
Party?

1378
03:34:54.020 --> 03:34:56.930
Yeah, on Long Island.

1379
03:34:58.030 --> 03:35:01.600
A Secretary Bailey.

1380
03:35:05.030 --> 03:35:07.610
Do you know Secretary Bailey?

1381
03:35:09.040 --> 03:35:10.660
No.

1382
03:35:12.670 --> 03:35:15.410
But I was invited anyway.

1383
03:35:23.510 --> 03:35:26.560
If you don't know each other,
why were you invited?

1384
03:35:26.560 --> 03:35:28.500
I don't know.

1385
03:35:29.730 --> 03:35:32.180
I thought you might know why.

1386
03:35:32.810 --> 03:35:34.400
Me?

1387
03:35:34.400 --> 03:35:36.430
Why me?

1388
03:35:41.440 --> 03:35:43.770
Because you know him.

1389
03:35:44.820 --> 03:35:46.450
- Who is it?
- David.

1390
03:35:46.450 --> 03:35:49.330
- No, David.
- Can I come in?

1391
03:35:49.330 --> 03:35:52.370
No. Just wait outside,
I'll call you.

1392
03:35:52.370 --> 03:35:55.150
Okay, I'll be right here.

1393
03:35:57.540 --> 03:36:01.550
- What does Bailey want from me?
- You came to ask me that?

1394
03:36:01.550 --> 03:36:04.720
- Why'd he send me an invitation?
- I don't know.

1395
03:36:04.720 --> 03:36:09.260
Why should I know about your
invitations? I don't know anything.

1396
03:36:09.260 --> 03:36:13.440
What do you want? Why did you come
here? I know nothing.

1397
03:36:13.440 --> 03:36:16.510
Now you're a lousy actress.

1398
03:36:18.940 --> 03:36:22.190
Who is Secretary Bailey?

1399
03:36:30.530 --> 03:36:34.570
Secretary Bailey
is a rich businessman.

1400
03:36:39.880 --> 03:36:44.670
He came to the United States as an
immigrant and made a lot of money...

1401
03:36:44.670 --> 03:36:48.800
...in San Francisco and L.A.,
where he's lived for 30 years.

1402
03:36:48.800 --> 03:36:53.210
I know all that. It's all
in the papers. What else is there?

1403
03:36:59.310 --> 03:37:02.720
He married a very wealthy woman.

1404
03:37:03.610 --> 03:37:06.320
They had a child.

1405
03:37:06.320 --> 03:37:09.950
She died when the child was born.

1406
03:37:09.950 --> 03:37:14.660
A few years ago, he went
into politics. Moved here.

1407
03:37:14.660 --> 03:37:19.870
That's history. I'm not talking
about that. I'm talking about now.

1408
03:37:19.870 --> 03:37:22.900
Right now he's in trouble.

1409
03:37:24.170 --> 03:37:27.720
Just tell me you've been living
with him all these years,

1410
03:37:27.720 --> 03:37:30.090
and you're his lover.

1411
03:37:38.520 --> 03:37:41.920
Age can wither me, Noodles.

1412
03:37:45.230 --> 03:37:48.260
We're both getting old.

1413
03:37:53.200 --> 03:37:56.900
All that we have left now
are our memories.

1414
03:37:59.410 --> 03:38:05.780
If you go to that party on Saturday
night, you won't have those anymore.

1415
03:38:06.750 --> 03:38:09.620
Tear up that invitation.

1416
03:38:11.590 --> 03:38:14.620
There's an exit back this way.

1417
03:38:15.140 --> 03:38:18.460
Noodles, go through it.

1418
03:38:20.720 --> 03:38:22.810
Keep walking.

1419
03:38:22.810 --> 03:38:25.470
Don't turn around.

1420
03:38:26.400 --> 03:38:28.730
Please, Noodles.

1421
03:38:28.730 --> 03:38:32.140
I'm begging you. Please.

1422
03:38:38.200 --> 03:38:42.150
Are you afraid that I'll turn
into a pillar of salt?

1423
03:38:45.250 --> 03:38:49.410
If you go out that door, yes.

1424
03:39:47.220 --> 03:39:50.400
This is Secretary Bailey's son.

1425
03:39:50.400 --> 03:39:54.300
His name's David, just like yours.

1426
03:42:26.340 --> 03:42:32.010
I must admit this party was
a wonderful idea, Mr. Secretary.

1427
03:42:32.010 --> 03:42:35.720
It's a bit like saying, "I'm going
up before the Commettee in 5 days,

1428
03:42:35.720 --> 03:42:38.350
like, my conscience is clear.

1429
03:42:38.350 --> 03:42:42.480
The most important people
in New York are my guests.

1430
03:42:42.480 --> 03:42:45.770
It's going to be a night
to remember."

1431
03:42:45.770 --> 03:42:48.350
Especially if the house blows up.

1432
03:42:48.820 --> 03:42:51.350
Where are you putting the next bomb?

1433
03:42:52.450 --> 03:42:54.600
In the freezer?

1434
03:42:55.200 --> 03:42:57.520
Or in the toilet?

1435
03:43:05.210 --> 03:43:08.580
You can't even think straight
anymore.

1436
03:43:09.300 --> 03:43:11.670
I'll tell you something.

1437
03:43:11.670 --> 03:43:16.830
A waiting list of people would like
to send flowers to your funeral.

1438
03:43:18.600 --> 03:43:22.390
- I can point out ten right now,
if you like me to. -Yes.

1439
03:43:22.390 --> 03:43:25.520
But none of them wants to read my
obituary in front of the Committee

1440
03:43:25.520 --> 03:43:27.690
as much as you do.

1441
03:43:27.690 --> 03:43:29.890
You and your union.

1442
03:43:32.940 --> 03:43:35.860
We just want to resolve
this situation clean.

1443
03:43:35.860 --> 03:43:39.570
I've heard that same song from you
for 35 fucking years!

1444
03:43:39.570 --> 03:43:42.350
Who do you think you are talking to?

1445
03:43:43.620 --> 03:43:47.420
I helped you to make a fortune,
you and the rest of those parasites!

1446
03:43:47.420 --> 03:43:52.410
It was a reasonable arrangement
between labour and management.

1447
03:43:53.420 --> 03:43:57.260
2% for them and 40% for you.

1448
03:43:57.260 --> 03:44:01.010
You defend them and you screw them.
Come on!

1449
03:44:01.010 --> 03:44:03.630
It's been the story of your life.

1450
03:44:04.220 --> 03:44:07.880
- Do you think anybody believe you
anymore? -Some.

1451
03:44:08.520 --> 03:44:11.190
But no one believes in you anymore,

1452
03:44:11.190 --> 03:44:14.640
because you have made mistakes
and I haven't.

1453
03:44:15.610 --> 03:44:18.690
But that's beside the point.

1454
03:44:20.110 --> 03:44:23.080
The important thing right now
is that

1455
03:44:23.080 --> 03:44:26.780
you and I straighten out
these transfers of authority.

1456
03:44:28.790 --> 03:44:31.540
Now it's all as we have agreed.

1457
03:44:34.420 --> 03:44:37.370
Have had our lawyers drawn it up.

1458
03:44:39.010 --> 03:44:41.710
All you have to do is sign.

1459
03:44:49.600 --> 03:44:51.930
My last will?

1460
03:44:53.150 --> 03:44:56.300
You are not in a position
to exercise your will.

1461
03:44:58.530 --> 03:45:01.230
I give up everything.

1462
03:45:02.610 --> 03:45:05.530
12% would be set aside for your boy.

1463
03:45:05.530 --> 03:45:10.270
In that way he can be assured
of living to a ripe old age.

1464
03:45:10.950 --> 03:45:14.160
Or not, if I don't sign?

1465
03:46:24.400 --> 03:46:27.650
Why don't you take care of this
by yourself?

1466
03:46:28.660 --> 03:46:32.200
I'd be very happy for you tonight,
if during all the noise of the party

1467
03:46:32.200 --> 03:46:35.610
- I heard a shot.
- Maybe you will.

1468
03:47:47.940 --> 03:47:50.190
Please go in.

1469
03:48:03.830 --> 03:48:06.580
What are you waiting for?

1470
03:48:09.840 --> 03:48:12.910
I don't understand, Mr. Bailey.

1471
03:48:38.990 --> 03:48:41.490
Sit down, Noodles.

1472
03:48:45.330 --> 03:48:47.530
Make yourself comfortable.

1473
03:49:05.520 --> 03:49:08.390
I'm glad you accepted my invitation.

1474
03:49:08.390 --> 03:49:10.800
Well, I was curious.

1475
03:49:13.360 --> 03:49:16.690
So many important people
in one place.

1476
03:49:16.690 --> 03:49:21.030
Yes. Well, the rats usually
desert a sinking ship.

1477
03:49:21.030 --> 03:49:25.360
But in my case, they appear to be
flocking onboard.

1478
03:49:36.590 --> 03:49:40.820
Yeah, well, I read about
your troubles in the newspapers.

1479
03:49:41.800 --> 03:49:43.760
But a man in your position,

1480
03:49:43.760 --> 03:49:46.680
with all your power
and all your privileges...

1481
03:49:46.680 --> 03:49:51.600
...has to assume a certain amount
of responsibility...

1482
03:49:51.600 --> 03:49:54.470
...a certain amount of risk.

1483
03:50:01.530 --> 03:50:04.680
Why'd you ask me
to come here, Mr. Bailey?

1484
03:50:07.620 --> 03:50:12.500
That invitation doesn't mean
a goddamn thing, and you know it.

1485
03:50:12.500 --> 03:50:16.450
All that counts is what
was in that suitcase.

1486
03:50:17.710 --> 03:50:20.830
The money and the contract.

1487
03:50:23.260 --> 03:50:26.870
It didn't say who the contract
was on, though.

1488
03:50:27.800 --> 03:50:30.630
Haven't you figured that out yet?

1489
03:50:31.930 --> 03:50:33.880
You, Mr. Bailey?

1490
03:50:47.280 --> 03:50:51.390
I haven't had a gun in my hand
for many, many years.

1491
03:50:52.620 --> 03:50:58.580
My eyes aren't too good, even
with my glasses. My hands shake.

1492
03:51:01.050 --> 03:51:05.450
- And I wouldn't want to miss.
- Cut the bullshit, Noodles.

1493
03:51:06.590 --> 03:51:09.750
I'm already a dead man.

1494
03:51:10.260 --> 03:51:15.350
At least give me the chance to
settle the debt that I owe to you.

1495
03:51:15.350 --> 03:51:19.020
I'll never make it before
the investigating committee.

1496
03:51:19.020 --> 03:51:23.360
They're scared I'll implicate
the whole bunch of 'em.

1497
03:51:23.360 --> 03:51:25.980
They gotta get rid of me.

1498
03:51:28.240 --> 03:51:31.610
Today is as good a day as any.

1499
03:51:33.530 --> 03:51:36.160
You do it, Noodles.

1500
03:51:36.700 --> 03:51:40.490
You're the only person
I can accept it from.

1501
03:51:46.960 --> 03:51:49.720
You see, I found out where you were.

1502
03:51:49.720 --> 03:51:53.200
I brought you back here for this.

1503
03:51:54.140 --> 03:51:57.750
To even the score
between you and me.

1504
03:51:59.730 --> 03:52:02.600
You can get out through there.

1505
03:52:09.440 --> 03:52:14.400
It leads right down to the street.
Nobody will see you.

1506
03:52:20.750 --> 03:52:25.530
I don't know what you're talking
about. You don't owe me a thing.

1507
03:52:33.090 --> 03:52:37.760
Your eyes were too full of tears
to see it wasn't me burned up

1508
03:52:37.760 --> 03:52:39.630
on that street.

1509
03:52:40.060 --> 03:52:42.340
It was somebody else.

1510
03:52:43.520 --> 03:52:49.070
You were too shocked to realize
that the cops were in on it too.

1511
03:52:49.070 --> 03:52:52.680
That was a syndicate operation,
Noodles.

1512
03:53:02.580 --> 03:53:04.980
You're crazy.

1513
03:53:07.040 --> 03:53:11.590
You said that to me once before,
a long time ago.

1514
03:53:11.590 --> 03:53:15.800
My mind was never as clear
as it was at that moment.

1515
03:53:15.800 --> 03:53:19.510
I took away your whole life
from you.

1516
03:53:19.510 --> 03:53:22.760
I've been living in your place.

1517
03:53:23.600 --> 03:53:26.600
I took everything.

1518
03:53:27.600 --> 03:53:30.480
I took your money.

1519
03:53:30.480 --> 03:53:33.320
I took your girl.

1520
03:53:33.320 --> 03:53:38.520
All I left for you was 35 years
of grief over having killed me.

1521
03:53:39.950 --> 03:53:42.150
Now, why don't you shoot?

1522
03:55:16.380 --> 03:55:19.500
It's true,
I have killed people, Mr. Bailey.

1523
03:55:19.500 --> 03:55:24.550
Sometimes to defend myself.
Sometimes for money.

1524
03:55:24.550 --> 03:55:27.300
And many people used to come to us.

1525
03:55:27.300 --> 03:55:30.600
Business partners, rivals...

1526
03:55:30.600 --> 03:55:33.140
...lovers.

1527
03:55:33.140 --> 03:55:37.680
Some of the jobs we took,
and some we didn't.

1528
03:55:50.660 --> 03:55:54.030
Yours is one we would never touch.

1529
03:55:54.500 --> 03:55:57.870
Is this your way of getting revenge?

1530
03:56:01.420 --> 03:56:03.410
No.

1531
03:56:06.340 --> 03:56:09.870
It's just the way I see things.

1532
03:57:12.160 --> 03:57:15.360
It's 10:25...

1533
03:57:16.240 --> 03:57:19.820
...and I've got nothing left
to lose.

1534
03:57:21.540 --> 03:57:25.900
When you've been betrayed
by a friend, you hit back.

1535
03:57:30.550 --> 03:57:32.790
Do it.

1536
03:57:54.530 --> 03:57:57.560
You see, Mr. Secretary...

1537
03:57:59.160 --> 03:58:01.650
...I have a story also.

1538
03:58:02.200 --> 03:58:05.150
A little simpler than yours.

1539
03:58:05.870 --> 03:58:10.990
Many years ago I had a friend,
a dear friend.

1540
03:58:12.210 --> 03:58:15.670
I turned him in to save his life...

1541
03:58:15.670 --> 03:58:18.380
...but he was killed.

1542
03:58:19.260 --> 03:58:22.510
But he wanted it that way.

1543
03:58:23.140 --> 03:58:25.760
It was a great friendship.

1544
03:58:28.440 --> 03:58:32.890
It went bad for him,
and it went bad for me too.

1545
03:58:37.450 --> 03:58:40.020
Good night, Mr. Bailey.

1546
03:58:48.790 --> 03:58:52.900
I hope the investigation
turns out to be nothing.

1547
03:58:54.420 --> 03:58:58.870
It'd be a shame to see
a lifetime of work go to waste.

